article.headline: Bowling Green 81, Arkansas State 72
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Martin Samarco scored 29 points, including five 3-pointers, as Bowling Green defeated Arkansas State 81-72 Monday night. Bowling Green (4-2) never trailed during the game, jumping out to a 15-point halftime lead. The Falcons shot 52 percent for the game compared with 43 percent for Arkansas State (4-7). Ryne Hamblet had eight rebounds and 12 points for the Falcons, including a 3-pointer with 9:38 left to play that made the score 67-47 and gave Bowling Green its largest lead of the game. Arkansas State battled back to within eleven points with 2:11 remaining, but couldn't close the gap down the stretch. Samarco went 11-of-18 from the field and had 5 rebounds, and Erik Marschall went 6-of-8 from the field and finished with 14 points. Dusan Radivojevic had 10 points and five rebounds and Ryan Sims scored eleven. The Indians' Adrian Banks led all scorers with 32 points, but he was the only Arkansas State player in double digits.
